reviews.review_text:
Great Sound!!! I downloaded this show on bt.etree.org along with 12-01-79 and 12-28-79.  The sound on this is incredable as is the playing.  I was not a big fan of '79 until now.  

Second set is amazing!  Dancin -> Franklins WOW!! Listen and/or get it.

Jeez Charlie! If you want to see why i strictly search for this crazy son of a gun's work in the dead archive, compare versions of this show. This show is great, 79 on point. But, you know it's true when you listen to this version...

THANK YOU CHARLIE, ONCE AGAIN, THANK YOU!

If the archive is like a drug, i am an addict, and Charlie Miller has the maximum potency. Charlie my man...

SICK

Dancin' The sound is REAL good as you can expect from Miller.
Set I: Pass it by. Some good moments, but nothing special. Phil is strong.
Set II: Wow! The whole thing. Especially Dancin'> Franklins and The Other One. Maybe the best Dancing ever - and I love the ones from '70. Phil booms the intro to The Other One 3 times! Don't miss it.

*Astonishing* Sound- Legendary Show... There are NO words for the Dancin' thru The Other segment...  Amazing.

Equally amazing is Charlie Miller's talent in bringing to us the best quality possible.

God bless you, Mr. Miller, where ever you are....

I hear the night before was a great show as well, (although much less known)

I must hunt down that China/Rider

Sweet Sound Quality Excellent sound quality.

This is one of the shows on the upcoming "30 Trips" release.

The sound is not only sweet and crisp, but also well balanced.    You can hear all the instruments equally.

not really a 'caution' jam GREAT show. Jack, Dancin-frankie roll away, he's gone jam, other one plus good sound, bass etc

but the 'caution' jam is good just not really caution. Listen to the Boston Garden 'caution' jam from 5/80. Phil was full on  'Caution' the best  post 74. The Nassau 81 ditto. Not really 'caution' but a GOOD Jam. Ill listen to that one again its been a few years
